# Lab Instructions â€” Password Cracking (John the Ripper & Hashcat)

## 1) Prepare hash file (lab-only)
- Create a small file `sample_hashes/hashes.txt` containing the target hashes. Example (MD5 plaintext->hash example for lab):
  - Hash lines *only* (one per line), no usernames unless format requires.

## 2) John the Ripper (local)
### Install (Kali / Debian)
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y john

# decompress rockyou if present
sudo gunzip /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt.gz || true
# run john with rockyou and rules
john --wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt --rules --format=raw-md5 sample_hashes/hashes.txt --pot=results/john.pot
# show cracked
john --show --pot=results/john.pot sample_hashes/hashes.txt > results/john_cracked.txt
